Subject: [PATCH 3/3] set CROSS_SYSTEM_HEADER_DIR

I'm not sure why the CLFS book did it this way, as apposed to using whatever
configure flag sets CROSS_SYSTEM_HEADER_DIR... but I might as well follow
suit.
---
 gcc/Makefile.in |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/gcc/Makefile.in b/gcc/Makefile.in
index ae2416b..37151f0 100644
--- a/gcc/Makefile.in
+++ b/gcc/Makefile.in
@@ -440,7 +440,7 @@ LTO_SYMTAB_H = $(srcdir)/../include/lto-symtab.h
 # Default native SYSTEM_HEADER_DIR, to be overridden by targets.
 NATIVE_SYSTEM_HEADER_DIR = /usr/include
 # Default cross SYSTEM_HEADER_DIR, to be overridden by targets.
-CROSS_SYSTEM_HEADER_DIR = @CROSS_SYSTEM_HEADER_DIR@
+CROSS_SYSTEM_HEADER_DIR = /bootstrap/include
 
 # autoconf sets SYSTEM_HEADER_DIR to one of the above.
 # Purge it of unneccessary internal relative paths
